---
---

<section class="py-24 px-4">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">

    <h2 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-zinc-100 text-center mb-4">
      Generic AI is worse than no AI.
    </h2>
    <p class="text-zinc-500 text-center text-base max-w-lg mx-auto mb-16">
      You spend more time managing the tool than using it.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-16">

      <!-- P1: doesn't know your clients -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
        <div class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-xl p-6 relative overflow-hidden">
          <div class="text-amber-400/20 font-display font-bold text-7xl absolute top-2 right-4 leading-none select-none pointer-events-none" aria-hidden="true">01</div>
          <div class="text-amber-400 font-display font-bold text-xl mb-3 relative z-10">01</div>
          <p class="text-zinc-300 text-base leading-relaxed relative z-10">
            <span class="font-semibold text-zinc-100">"It doesn't know your clients."</span><br />
            You re-explain your context every session. Consultants briefing AI on the same accounts. Coaches re-entering client history. Founders recapping pilot customers and investor relationships. Every time.
          </p>
        </div>
        <blockquote class="border-l-2 border-zinc-800 pl-3">
          <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm italic leading-relaxed">"I got tired of Claude Code forgetting all my context every time I open a new session."</p>
          <!-- source: Hacker News (2026) -->
        </blockquote>
      </div>

      <!-- P2: DIY fell apart -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
        <div class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-xl p-6 relative overflow-hidden">
          <div class="text-amber-400/20 font-display font-bold text-7xl absolute top-2 right-4 leading-none select-none pointer-events-none" aria-hidden="true">02</div>
          <div class="text-amber-400 font-display font-bold text-xl mb-3 relative z-10">02</div>
          <p class="text-zinc-300 text-base leading-relaxed relative z-10">You tried building a system yourself. It took a weekend, worked for two weeks, then fell apart when your projects changed.</p>
        </div>
        <blockquote class="border-l-2 border-zinc-800 pl-3">
          <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm italic leading-relaxed">"You're not thinking — you're maintaining. Your time shifts from creating knowledge to building the machine that might someday help you retrieve it."</p>
          <!-- source: Medium (2025) -->
          <cite class="text-zinc-600 text-xs not-italic mt-1 block">— Medium</cite>
        </blockquote>
      </div>

      <!-- P3: starts from zero -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
        <div class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-xl p-6 relative overflow-hidden">
          <div class="text-amber-400/20 font-display font-bold text-7xl absolute top-2 right-4 leading-none select-none pointer-events-none" aria-hidden="true">03</div>
          <div class="text-amber-400 font-display font-bold text-xl mb-3 relative z-10">03</div>
          <p class="text-zinc-300 text-base leading-relaxed relative z-10">Every session starts from zero. Your AI has no memory of what you built last month, who you talked to, or what you decided.</p>
        </div>
        <blockquote class="border-l-2 border-zinc-800 pl-3">
          <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm italic leading-relaxed">"Whatever the internal state is of Claude Code, it's lost as soon as you /clear or close the Terminal window."</p>
          <!-- source: Hacker News -->
          <cite class="text-zinc-600 text-xs not-italic mt-1 block">— Hacker News</cite>
        </blockquote>
      </div>

    </div>

    <p class="text-center text-zinc-400 text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      AI systems decay without maintenance.
      <span class="text-zinc-100 font-medium"> BrainKit is your maintenance contract.</span>
    </p>

  </div>
</section>
